9
00:00:22,000 --> 00:00:25,000
What? How?

10
00:00:25,000 --> 00:00:27,000
Morning, Stanley.

11
00:00:27,000 --> 00:00:32,000
There's this thing that people tend to do with billboards.

12
00:00:32,000 --> 00:00:34,000
How do I put this?

13
00:00:34,000 --> 00:00:44,000
If there's an opportunity for a graffiti artist to work in a phallic shape, interacting with the artwork, it'll happen.

14
00:00:44,000 --> 00:00:48,000
And Andy gave them that opportunity.

15
00:00:48,000 --> 00:00:51,000
Erin, how long do we order those billboards for?

16
00:00:51,000 --> 00:00:52,000
Six months.

17
00:00:52,000 --> 00:00:54,000
Oh, good. I need you to call the billboard company.

18
00:00:54,000 --> 00:00:59,000
Great billboard. Funny, edgy, right up to the line without crossing it. Loved it.

19
00:00:59,000 --> 00:01:00,000
Which one did you see?

20
00:01:00,000 --> 00:01:02,000
Washington Street, the one with like 20 dogs on it.

21
00:01:02,000 --> 00:01:04,000
Okay, don't be gross.

22
00:01:04,000 --> 00:01:05,000
What's going on?

23
00:01:05,000 --> 00:01:08,000
Somebody defaced the billboards we just put out in an inappropriate way.

24
00:01:08,000 --> 00:01:10,000
Oh, that's funny.

25
00:01:10,000 --> 00:01:15,000
Wade, from the photo shoot with you and me?

26
00:01:15,000 --> 00:01:17,000
Yeah, Dwight.

27
00:01:17,000 --> 00:01:20,000
No. No.

28
00:01:20,000 --> 00:01:32,000
No, no!

29
00:01:50,000 --> 00:01:58,800
Shrewd Farms is very easy to find.

30
00:01:58,800 --> 00:02:00,520
It's right in the middle of the root vegetable district.

31
00:02:00,520 --> 00:02:03,640
If the soil starts to get acidic, you've probably gone too far.

32
00:02:03,640 --> 00:02:04,640
Just give us the address.

33
00:02:04,640 --> 00:02:05,640
We'll look it up online.

34
00:02:05,640 --> 00:02:06,640
